{"type":"message","id":"0d3b415f","parentId":"27db5d36","timestamp":"2026-04-27T20:19:24.671Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I found the email chain. The thread shows the conversation between Bobby and RC Leasing (Royal Cove). Bobby sent an email on April 25 saying he completed his portion of the application and is waiting on Logan. Then RC Leasing replied asking when they want to move by, and Bobby replied on April 27 saying they were hoping for before June 4th and will follow up once Logan completes his portion.\n\nThe most recent email (April 27, 2026) from RC Leasing says they may have one for that timeframe but they're first come first serve, and once Logan is done they can begin the process.\n\nSo yes Bobby, I can see the email you sent! You sent an email on April 25, 2026 at 1:49 PM to RC Leasing at Royal Cove saying you completed your portion of the rental application and were waiting on Logan.","thinkingSignature":"a0a15412b06ae0b26ef0bacbfb486423ded9d60c0a95d8e52909cbf27dcd99f1"},{"type":"text","text":"Yes Bobby, I found it! You sent this email on **April 25, 2026 at 1:49 PM**:\n\n> Hi Amy,\n>\n> I wanted to reach out to let you know that I have completed and submitted my portion of the rental application for Royal Cove. I am currently waiting on my partner, Logan, to finish his part of the application on his end.\n>\n> We are still very interested in a 1 bedroom / 1 bathroom unit. Please let me know if you need anything else from me in the meantime, or if there are any updates on availability.\n>\n> Thank you,\n> Robert Galletta\n\nRC Leasing (Amy Smith) replied on **April 27** saying they may have a unit for that timeframe, but reminded you it's first come first serve and once Logan completes his portion, they can run the applications."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":9883,"output":358,"cacheRead":25228,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":35469,"cost":{"in