{"type":"message","id":"1eb4e5ca","parentId":"4ccbc476","timestamp":"2026-04-27T20:20:43.150Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so the IDs 8, 7, 6, 5 are Bobby's emails to Royal Cove. The message read command earlier returned different messages when I used -- 8 and -- 7. That's because the `--` argument is for message ID not envelope ID. And apparently the message IDs don't match the envelope IDs.\n\nLet me try using the envelope IDs differently. Actually, looking at the himalaya message read syntax, it seems like it takes a message ID number. Maybe the envelope IDs and message IDs are different. \n\nActually, let me look at the thread command differently. Or maybe I should try `himalaya envelope thread` with a proper query.\n\nWait - when I tried `himalaya envelope thread --account icloud --folder \"Sent Messages\" -- 8`, it said \"cannot parse search emails query `8`\". \n\nSo `thread` expects a search query, not a message ID. But `message read` takes an ID from the mailbox. Let me try a different approach and search for the most recent email to RC Leasing directly using a query like `to RCLeasing@lexingtonpg.com`.","thinkingSignature":"6ddcc25b227fd2fbc41565ec06700fc38aad8c4e5e750df9a3a20ef200d0c1ce"},{"type":"text","text":"Let me search directly for emails to RC Leasing:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_49pb3a5xvs80_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"himalaya envelope list --account icloud --folder \"Sent Messages\" \"to RCLeasing@lexingtonpg.com\" --page-size 10 -o json 2>/dev/null 2>&1","timeout":20}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":13349,"output":323,"cacheRead":25228,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":38900,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777321233411,"responseId":"063ef811245e50b0c8d2964a2929a41f"}}
