{"type":"message","id":"a42aa9a9","parentId":"7c6ff1f7","timestamp":"2026-04-27T20:21:22.248Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK. I see the folder is named \"Sent Messages\" but the message read command doesn't accept a folder argument. \n\nWait - when I did `himalaya message read --account icloud -- 7`, it returned the email from RC Leasing (the one about amenities). But that was in the INBOX. \n\nActually wait - when I read message 7, it showed the content from RC Leasing TO Bobby, not from Bobby to RC. That doesn't make sense for a sent folder message ID. Unless... maybe message IDs are global across the account, not per-folder?\n\nActually, looking back at my earlier read of message ID 7, it showed From: RC Leasing TO: Bobby - that was a received email, not a sent one. So the message IDs might be globally sequential across the account, not folder-specific.\n\nSo when I want to read sent messages, I might need a different approach. Let me think...\n\nMaybe I should use the `himalaya envelope list` with subject \"Re: Looking for new apartment\" and then use the IDs from that to construct a query. The IDs 8 and 7 in the sent folder ARE the right ones. But when I read them, I get different content.\n\nWait - I just realized something. When I read message 7, I got the RC Leasing email about amenities. When I read message 8, I got the same thread showing the April 25 email. \n\nHmm but actually - let me look at what I actually read. When I read message 7, the output started with \"From: RC Leasing\" and had the full email chain including \"From: Bobby Galletta\" at the bottom. So it showed the whole thread. And when I read message 8, it also showed From: RC Leasing with the full chain.\n\nBut these were both readable emails, not errors. So maybe the message IDs do correspond to the right emails, but what I'm seeing is the full email thread because himalaya expands threads or something?\n \nActually, I'm realizing the envelope IDs and message IDs are separate systems. The envelope list showed me IDs 5, 6, 7, 8 for sent messages, but when I try to read using those IDs, I'm getting different emails entirely. The message read command might be pulling from a different folder or using a different indexing system altogether.\n\nWait—when I read message ID 7, I got an email FROM RC Leasing TO Bobby, which means that ID actually belongs to an inbox message, not a sent message. So message IDs are clearly not mapped directly to sent folder positions. The only sent email I can actually confirm exists is message 8, which I've already seen displayed as part of a thread. I should try searching the inbox by subject line to find the sent email instead of relying on sequential ID lookups.","thinkingSignature":"014185af188a5e46262a15e843960f86da42d0c7d82552e5c07d4278abf86012"},{"type":"text","text":"Let me try searching for your sent email by date:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_iml57wpkhf27_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"himalaya envelope list --account icloud --folder \"Sent Messages\" \"date 2026-04-27\" --page-size 20 -o json 2>/dev/null 2>&1","timeout":20}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":15464,"output":670,"cacheRead":25228,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":41362,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777321265868,"responseId":"063ef8319975b0d2a59767f5875ffee1"}}
